                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16748459" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 07:39:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you run &lt;tt&gt;mvn clean package javadoc:aggregate&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;it still gives the error, but javadoc is generated.&lt;br/&gt;
IIRC MANIFEST.MF files are only being read from jars, not directories.&lt;br/&gt;
There is still something wrong, not sure what.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16748857" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 15:54:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The error is coming from Maven, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/blob/1db2917d21e9eb4f338bae75d886f164369e392f/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/plugins/javadoc/AbstractJavadocMojo.java#L4935-L4962&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;AbstractJavadocMojo.java#L4935-L4962&lt;/a&gt; so that needs to be fixed.&lt;br/&gt;
Apart from that I think the javadoc command works as expected, as long as you ensure that the automatic module is available as a jar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16748873" author="cowwoc" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 16:08:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the user runs without a JAR and the goal fails with the aforementioned error, is it possible for the plugin to scan for &lt;tt&gt;Automatic-Module-Name&lt;/tt&gt; in the manifest and give the user a better error message (e.g. &quot;you need to invoke the &lt;tt&gt;package&lt;/tt&gt; goal prior to &lt;tt&gt;javadoc:aggregate&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;for automatic modules&quot;)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16748894" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 16:40:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is probably more important that in case of at least 1 modular jar, that all others are modules as well, no matter where the name is coming from. And let&apos;s add some documentation for this usecase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16748921" author="cowwoc" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 17:14:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rfscholte&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rfscholte&quot;&gt;rfscholte&lt;/a&gt; Unfortunately, that is not always possible. In my case, my multi-module Maven project contains a mix of modular JARs and maven plugins. Maven plugins cannot be defined in a modular JAR. Hence my use of &lt;tt&gt;Automatic-Module-Name&lt;/tt&gt;. That&apos;s the closest I can get.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do we do in this case? Is there a way to &quot;promote&quot; the Maven plugin module to a modular JAR from the perspective of the Javadoc to avoid this error?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16748939" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 17:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, the confusion &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I must be better with my wording: All Maven modules must have an explicit  Java module name, either from the module descriptor or from the Automatic-Module-Name. I must test it with a filename based modulename.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16748952" author="cowwoc" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 17:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good&#160;&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&#160;I&apos;ll wait on your update to re-test the &quot;unpackaged Automatic-Module-Name&quot; use-case since that seems to be the hardest case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16749268" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2019 23:09:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;new snapshot available, code changes reviewable at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/commit/76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/commit/76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16749486" author="cowwoc" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2019 04:13:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The change is quite good. I just have one small suggestion: consider referencing the documentation found at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/commit/76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e#diff-674685ece2559534316adfc00c30c62aR175&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/commit/76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e#diff-674685ece2559534316adfc00c30c62aR175&lt;/a&gt;&#160;from the error message found at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/commit/76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e#diff-b6a9572abea55bd3a9acdb0e381f94f9R4977&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/commit/76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e#diff-b6a9572abea55bd3a9acdb0e381f94f9R4977&lt;/a&gt;. I think&#160;it would help users understand what you mean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now for the bad news. I just discovered two new bugs: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-568&quot; title=&quot;javadoc:jar fails when project has Automatic-Module-Name and (implicit) uses offlinelinks with element-list&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-568&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-568&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-569&quot; title=&quot;javadoc:aggregate fails with &amp;#39;error: package org.w3c.dom is not visible&amp;#39; when mixing Java modules and non-modules&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The latter is very nasty. Consider taking a look at it first because it&apos;ll affect all the work you&apos;ve done to date. Sorry in advance &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16750287" author="rfscholte" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2019 18:11:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We used to refer to webpages when there was an exception, but pages are too dynamic. In fact, it was pointing to mojo.codehaus.org long after this domain was killed. So I&apos;d prefer not to do so. Let Google and Stack Overflow to their work &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16750359" author="rfscholte" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2019 19:22:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=maven-javadoc-plugin.git;a=commit;h=76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;76137502a55064e3914f578c0d8d75c375cbba7e&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16750395" author="hudson" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2019 20:00:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Build succeeded in Jenkins: Maven TLP &#187; maven-javadoc-plugin &#187; master #137&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-javadoc-plugin/job/master/137/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/maven-box/job/maven-javadoc-plugin/job/master/137/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17957954" author="olamy" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 05:09:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/issues/850&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-javadoc-plugin#850&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
